Reasoning: The paper deals with the correspondence between linear logic and the pi-calculus, which falls under the category of process calculi and formal languages (cs.PL). It also introduces a new interpretation of this correspondence, which involves hyperenvironments and hypersequents, which could be classified under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses denotational semantics and bisimilarity, which are topics in formal methods and verification (cs.SE). The use of Brzozowski derivatives in the denotational semantics could also place the paper under the category of formal language theory (cs.FL). Finally, the paper presents a fully abstract semantics, which could be relevant to the category of machine learning (cs.LG) in terms of developing more accurate models and algorithms.
